  - **Why: There is a use case for a body xlarge link. We currently have link tokens for small, default and large but not for xlarge. Additionally the scaling of the body tokens would be eased a bit by adjusting the body/xlarge tokens ( see to the right) When reviewing that ask, there was a bug discovered within link component where for two lines of content the line only underlines the second line. This is only fixable by utilizing a typography token with the underline decoration.** (Type: TEXT, ID: 7120:3368)
    - Text Content: "Why:

There is a use case for a body xlarge link. We currently have link tokens for small, default and large but not for xlarge. 

Additionally the scaling of the body tokens would be eased a bit by adjusting the body/xlarge tokens ( see to the right) 

When reviewing that ask, there was a bug discovered within link component where for two lines of content the line only underlines the second line. This is only fixable by utilizing a typography token with the underline decoration."

    - **tldr; yellow-50 works for evernorth, however none of the yellows work for cigna. that being said, orange is a good candidate for cigna. this considered a brand color. if we are okay with that. this is what we can move forward with. the only downside to this decision this that teams may ask why we cannot use the leaf-green accent color within the cigna palette for the success green utility color, and we will not have a great justification for saying no. evernorth uses hypermint (which is a brand color) for it’s utility colors. so we are already breaching this territory.** (Type: TEXT, ID: 10644:16244)
      - Text Content: "tldr; 
yellow-50 works for evernorth, 

however none of the yellows work for cigna.
that being said, orange is a good candidate for cigna. this considered a brand color. if we are okay with that. this is what we can move forward with. the only downside to this decision this that teams may ask why we cannot use the leaf-green accent color within the cigna palette for the success green utility color, and we will not have a great justification for saying no. evernorth uses hypermint (which is a brand color) for it’s utility colors. so we are already breaching this territory."
